Excellent

Very happy with this bank!

Signing up requires taking a photo of your passport (or other id). Problem is you need to be a professional photographer to take a photo that they'll accept! Eventually it tells you they need to chat but when chat opens nobody responds.

Truly a fantastic bank, I'm using it to help get me and my finances back on track, it's easy to use, tracks your payment, automatic budget calculator and advises you on how much to save etc, when I'm back to form I'll surely be setting my current account with monzo, I wish all banks operated like this but if they did we wouldn't have monzo Thank you very much Monzo.

I hope it'll be great but cant activate the card.. the app crashes when I try and there's no other way to activate it online or by phone. I've tried deleting and redownloading, no luck. Any suggestions??

Amazing, took less than 5 minutes to register. About 10 minutes later I picked up phone and I was a member. 5 more minutes I had a overdraft my bank would never give and set up the transfer from old one, got bank card that I not got yet setup on Google Pay. Started to verify PayPal and got notification instantly from Monzo. They beat the competition hands down, Starling took 48 hours to say application not accepted so clearly got a problem. I'm very impressed and that is not easy to do.
great app and service, only 4 stars because there's no weekly period for budgeting possible, which is frustrating
Excellent. Very useful.

I recently have moved to the UK and this bank has been a lifesaver. I could not get a conventional bank account due to lack of utility bills as they are included in my rent. Fantastic Interface and you can get paid a day early !!! Absolutely brilliant cant say good enough words
Good stuff. would be even better if you could change the reporting period e.g. weekly or fortnightly.
Perfect!
good bank and app!
Amazing
A beautiful user experience, innovative set of features and very impressive support. I have absolute faith in all that Monzo do. Great work guys!
Easy to follow up. Great customer service. Low fees .Super!

So far it has been great. Monzo verified my details quickly, and within 5 minutes I had a fully functional bank account. 2 business days later, I had the  card in a well-presented letter. And the app has been faultless, with instant notifications and easy to navigate.
this is what happens when innovation and free market looks like. great app, great service, great customer service. I always recommend.
Not had an issue, use it as my everyday card. Very good to use abroad, reasonable rates.

absolutely love everything about this bank. swapped over about a week ago and the amount of features it has available for free are insane. signed up for monzo plus so I can change my card colour because the default is disgusting haha

Great app/bank extreamly happy with this the card arrived in less than 48hrs! Easy to use and great that you can freeze your card and have saving pots with no minimum!

The bank itself was incredibly easy to set up and I was verified with in a matter of minutes. The app seems very user friendly and you are given the option to create lockable savings pots which are very handy for bad savers like myself! I set up this account for travelling as there are no fees for using it abroad and it can be used worldwide. Overall a very good first impression.

Have used the app for over 6 months on several continents, always works flawlessly. The bill splitting feature is a godsend when travelling with a large group or even just on a night out in London. However, the experience that got me to write this review is that less than 12 hours after having to be refunded for a hotel booking while in Canada the money was back in my account. compare that to the 3-5 business days at best that a high street bank would take.
really quiet cool apart from 2 payments going missong which after having a stroke and becoming d8ssabled over night I have been looked agftl
very bad app

DO NOT COMPLY WITH UK DATA REGULATIONS. I started the app, wanting to have a look at the products. Not available without applying - so i stopped. Requested Monzo delete data entered so far, they refused because they don't have the ability and won't for years, apparently. This is against UK data regulation. Complaint raised to ICO. If they openly admit they won'g follow the rules, how can they be trusted?
Always improving!
too many cases of account closure, lost money not yet refunded...monzo do you think business is run this way. close account and return customer's money is fair enough

Pretty pointless update comment. Is there an update? Isn't there? You're a bank. It makes me very suspicious when you issue frivolous, time-wasting updates like this. Are you hiding some security issue maybe? Are you just trying to grab attention? Well you've got my attention. Wondering now whether to complete the signup process or not. Wondering if you are trustworthy.

so far so good. wanted a banking option to save the change and better monitor what i spend. current Banking app doesn't have save the change and friend recommended this so we both got a fiver and it works perfectly

I understand why you have to do it for the first time, but asking you to send a picture of your id and take a video every time you need access to something is rediculous. ive dealt with a few banks and their apps and by far this is the most bothersome. I would not recommend. and I plan to leave.

Love the app and bank account. Had no issues using it, it's just like a normal bank! Would like to see some app security though, such as a pin or password to open the app. If someone else is using my phone I don't want them tapping the app and seeing all my incoming & outgoing payments aswell as my card details!
Perfect

App is very easy to use, customer service alternates between super fast and helpful or super slow and made up of generic/irrelevant copy and paste responses. Unlikely I'm going to use this card again.

I have used the same pin number at every bank I've been with but when I try to use it with monzo every ATM refuses to accept. Spoke to them on live chat which incidentally took a day to reply and basically they said tough they do not allow certain pin numbers to be used on their cards. Absolutely crazy!
very good mobile bank! fast process, all works very well with insta notification system. Well done!

As time progresses, Monzo has been becoming a little more like a real bank. In this case, it's a bad thing. They've scaled their marketing and now customer support is becoming generic, they are just trying to get rid of you, not help. Just like a bank.

love this bank I kept getting declined by a lot of banks but this bank gave me a shot and have never let me down since I've been with them in October greatways too see what's going out and coming in and u manage all your auto payments your self. customer service are always a great help I can not fault this bank they are brilliant

Every single time it goes to my email, g mail.I ve sign in with my yahoo account.What mean this????U have to keep the app running g all the time or u can't sign out....I sign out of my account and now is almost impossible to sign back in. ..

My sign up time took little over 10 minutes, which blew me away, some of the budgeting features are amazing and the transfer speed is instant. If you're sick and tired of banks that couldn't care less about you open a Monzo account, you won't regret it.

In the meantime, if you contact our Customer Operations team through the app, or via help@monzo.com, we can get you set up as soon as possible.

As a friend once said to me: "Can you crawl out of Monzo's arse for, like, five minutes?" I've had my card a little over a year, and have yet to discover a single issue. The app is intelligent and intuitive, the notifications help me keep track of my spending ("You've spent £*.** today") and reassure me I'd notice any fraudulent activity. Sending and receiving money is effortless, and customer service are quick and incredibly helpful. Free spending abroad alsi comes in incredibly helpful.

Only after I pointed my NFC reader right close to the chip, the card was then successfully detected. So I guest it's because of the tiny size of NFC tag antena designed for the card.

I use this to pay for things abroad and it's amazing. Usually end up getting a better rate than on Google or XE. I dunno how you guys do it but I love it!
Excellent app, would be handy to have more granularity in the reports such as amount spent in one country
Works great as a cheap way of spending abroad and budgeting your spend, with instant updates and top ups.
Great concept

Aaaaaand the main reason I moved to the bank has gone. Was looking forward to having the full current account, but now the free withdrawals abroad will be limited to £200 a month its a no from me. I'll be switching to Starling bank instead, which has these benefits. Was good while it lasted.
I cant get past step 2 of the verification process. :-(
Amazing bank!  We have saved many hundred of pound just with using this bank outside of UK. Great customer service as well. Thanks Monzo!
I was a little sceptical, especially with the £100 deposit, so glad I joined. Going from strength to strength. Received invite for current account a couple of weeks ago, A+
Waited weeks for a confirmation that my card was ready and now cannot open the app as per instructions.
Amazing app, really well designed. Rapid speed and accuracy for transactions.
Unbelievable customer support and slick app
Why I not can registration in Czech??? Why app joined me to Ukraine but I am locate in Praha !
A great prepaid card with no fees, and soon it will be a full bank account. App works very well, fast, easy to use and reliable.

Could not sign up. Mobile SMS works for initial install, but once card ready, SMS never arrives. Been trying for weeks . UPDATE issues all resolved. One of the best banking apps so far. Shows great promise. UPDATE. just gets better and better.

My first comment ever. I'm an exchange student and now spending my year abroad in Hong Kong. You can't even imagine how much less headache I have with monzo card which gives me the best exchange rate with 0 commissions and fees, and doesn't require any money transfers between UK and HK banks. Thank you so much for what you are doing, guys.
The bank the future. As soon as my Monzo current account is up and running I will be leaving Lloyd's​ Bank
Expenditure analysis is so good!
Love it. Really worked well in Morocco. No problems at all. excepted everywhere

66k people in front of me in the queue. Really not interested in 'the illusion of demand' like nightclubs. Especially when it comes to banking- no time for all that rubbish. Uninstall. You've lost me at Hello.
600000 people in front of me in the cue. Jog on
The future of banking. Love it.

I initially use Monzo only for traveling to avoid bank charges since Monzo has no charge and the currency rate is pretty good. But now I also use Monzo to separate my daily expenses from my saving accounts. I love the fact that I can track my expenses easily in Monzo. Keep up the good work.
The freezing feature is very useful, great exchange rate when used abroad and instant notifications when I spend helps me keep a closer eye on my money.
Excellent App, like most people I use the card mainly abroad to save on costs associated to withdrawing cash.

Do you think letting your users download app and waste time on registration only to find out later that it is UK ONLY makes users feel good? Neither the website nor Play state this... Now you got 1 star.
Not got my card, but a really good service
Needs £100 deposit. Before you even start.Instant uninstall.Junk company
Excellent. Used across Europe without any issues- both ATMs and general payments.
Used as a bank travel card in amsterdam. Easy to top up and money went to account instantly. Liked instant notifications of spending and cash withdrawals. Very good service

Honestly only signed up for this as a way to withdraw cash on holiday without a charge but been really impressed with it.  The app is really helpful and informative, and when I needed a quick change making the customer service team had it sorted way faster than I expected. Definitely recommend giving this a try, really is nothing to lose.
Total scam and waste of time. Must not be allowed to use the word Bank, as this app is just steeling emails and personal data, does not provide any banking or payment services actually.
Bit frustrated, two friends have signed up using my invite link, not moved up the waitlist a jot. Won't be sending any more :(
Great app for managing spending
This app does most things you'll need from your bank.
it was great i felt secured with my money when i was in the Philippines. Not needed to carry cash with me because i can use it almost everywhere. I just hope they can add android pay soon.
Moved from iOS to Android and feel theres room for improvement on this side, no fingerprint authentication required to access the app which is crucial to me.  Still love it though 😁
5 stars if they password protect the app when opening. Absolutely love Monzo though.
Love it and love how much info is in the community forums and public roadmap.
Best online banking app out Thier

Awesome app and excellent service. Compared to main street companies like Barclays the Monzo app makes them appear old and with no clue about this new fangled 'technology' thing.   Only slight wrinkle is Android users are second class, you have to wait a long time to get features iOS users got ages ago, if you even get them at all.
It's good but really needs some security login before displaying the status of the account. My wife just discovered how much I really spend on 'bargains'
Easy to track payments, instant notifications etc.. very good!
Amazing app, exactly what you need. And makes monitoring and working out what you spend so easy. Easy to transfer money in and out. Absolutely perfect
It would be even better if there was an easier tool to top up or transfer money into your account
Love Monzo. Splitting the bill is a fantastic thing

It's great but please add a %split graphic of all the categories like in the monify app. I can see how much i spend IN each category but not how much i spend ON each category. A total amount in each category would be useful too.
Amazing app but still needs to catch up compared to iOS version.
Used it in Italy September 2017 with no problems and was very fast telling you what and where spent and topped up instantly👍
Great for keeping track of your spending, with instant notifications and no pending payments. The app is extremely user friendly and the concept is exactly what modern banking needs. Love it
An amazing start to what could become the future of banking
Great app and spending updates are instant
Love Monzo. Definitely the future. App is great.
Doesn't take a picture so I can't verify my identity
All round brilliant app! Saved my life!

Such a disappointment. I expected an app that would not require 10 login attempts to set up. Then the force feeding of the debit card....wow guys, you have ruined this app. I don't care about the debit card. Why can't I just log in and register. I don't care about queues and sharing some hinge that I can use. Sad and overhyped.  Next.

Card arrived a day early. Pin sent to my phone. My 100 pounds was on the card AND THERE ARE NO FEES!. Spain, here I come and say goodbye to those 1euro 75 PLUS exchange rate or a minimum fee from the major Scumbanks!  Thank you for making this a card for the people. Hey guess what? I can even pay someones mobile phone and I can accept payments using my personal link...now that's not something other Scumbanks do. Well done monzo. Well done. I really hope you succeed and pass beta testing and launch Properly... please don't turn into the other greedy banks with excessive charges.
Really good app and good as a pre-pay account.  App is responsive and immediate updates for every transaction.

Excellent app, I like the instant notification and instant top up. I would like to able to do family accounting on it (include other card and other banks) and being able to export statements in pdf and accounting in Excel.  Thanks
Love it love it love it!!!
guys, you SHOULD let people know that you're UK-ONLY just BEFORE they sign up.

Excellent! I decided on a Monzo card to use abroad because there are no fees. Applying was easy (I used the link on MSE website to jump the queues) and card arrived 2 days later. Easy to use app, easy to top up, you can freeze the card via the app and the transactions show up instantly on the app. I needed to contact Monzo via Twitter as I had a question and they responded within 2 minutes. Great customer service!
Honestly? I can't wait for the Current Account. It feels incredibly strange to be excited about Banking/Money Management, but this is exactly what the industry needs.
I like  this app Make my Life easier....
Harshan
Was refused to fast track to the top of the queue on the awsummit event just because "Android is not supported yet".
column15: Hey Andril! If you update today, you should find you can sign up immediately and get your card 😄 We've been working hard on it and hope you like it.

column10: Love monzo, will love it more when android has the same features as iOS.

I'm a big fan of Monzo, makes my life easier not only abroad by saving on the exchange rates but also at home by making it easier to manage my daily spending. The customer support is outstanding which makes it stand out from all the competitors; professional, knowledgeable, quick and kind customer service reps. Recommended!
Used it in Portugal, fantastic! Worked great and the customer service is fast and helpful as well, bonus is no more coming back to a credit card bill, recommended.
Amazing! Simple easy and innovative! Lovely way to track and monitor spending.
Love it so simple to use as well.
Love my new card :)
Great app and service. One suggestion: could you please add customisable spending categories?
Amazing, but I wish I could use it as contactless on my Google Pixel

Great app, love the 'OMW card' - great touch! The UI is intuitive and simple, great seeing a clear breakdown of what I've been spending on and where - being able to add details and photos is a clever touch too. My only reservation, which is preventing 5 stars, is the lack of app login. All other banking apps require a password or fingerprint login, I love this and would like it to be an option in the settings. The reason for this is that my debit card is saved in-app and could be used to top up my Monzo card quite readily... Maybe not everyone is bothered by it, but for the fraction of a second it takes, it would give me piece of mind.  Overall, keep up the great work and I look forward to maybe having a current account with you one day, especially if it has a lairy-coloured card! Also, feel free to add in extra card animations, honestly that running card made my week!
Please make the app worldwide! It's useless for any other country than the UK!!

Monzo is 21st banking, built around a digital age. My wife and I both have a card, and we use it to manage our variable spend, ie food, fuel etc. Effectively we use it instead of cash, and if you are on a budget then the recommendation is to use cash, so you know exactly what you have to spend. This is precisely what you have with Monzo pre-pay mastercard.   What we love: -Ability to pop over money to each other, with no fees.  -Always know what you have to spend -Spend something and before you have your receipt you are notified in the app. Wherever you are in the world - Categories spend automatically, along with location - can lock the card quickly and easily, so it cannot be used.  - Support team via the in app chat are super fast at responding. Seen this with myself and a friend who also has Monzo.   You know it is a great app when you wife tells several friends how helpful Monzo is for budgeting, and they sign up.
Hands down best bank for foreign travel.

Great concept provided that the app works. I keep getting a "Screen overlay detected" error whenever I try to top up or send money to my friends. As a result, the card is not of much use to me at the moment.

This app just doesn't work on my Android tablet (Nexus 7). I have it working on my iPhone but I  can't make payments, send money etc on the tablet. My account info is correct and updates - but the app is totally non-functional in terms of contacts and payments.
Excellent, this had made taking money out while traveling so much easier and without the charges I would have incurred otherwise, I will be sticking with them as they develop.
Great app, really nice and user friendly interface. It would be helpful if we could change the categories of spendings as well create custom ones.

Used this card in America for 3 weeks. No charges and a great exchange rate! I lost my card towards the end off my trip and with one in app message they froze my card and sent out a new one.   It's excellent for monitoring spending   *****

Why the heck did you remove the top-up floating button ? Edit : Thanks for the clarification. I appreciate it. It does bring an extra click, but then the app has been flawless so far, while Revolut is always buggy. Thanks !
column15: Thanks for the feedback. We moved the top up button to prepare for our transition to current accounts. As current accounts will offer more options, we reorganised the app so features are grouped a little more logically (top up with card settings, sending money with your contacts), rather than overwhelming the home page with too many things.

column10: All good.
I love the Monzo card very functional amd easy to use but after deploying export data for iOS OVER A YEAR AGO I'm really annoyed it hasn't been deployed for Android.

I like it, but there are definitely some things on Revolut I prefer. First, on Revolut you can top up in precise amounts rather than increments of ten only. Second, I can pay my bank account/other people's bank accounts directly from my balance in-app on Revolut, something not possible on Monzo.   Also not great that there isn't a simple 'feedback' button on the app to write this somewhere!
column15: Thanks for the feedback, Frank. The good news is that we're working on transferring money to and from bank accounts at the moment, and both will be available (along with many other things) with the current accounts we'll be transitioning to over the next few months. Thanks again!

column10: Please bring back the top-up button for the home page!
Put top-up button back on home page.
column15: Thanks for the feedback, Stevie. We moved the top up button to prepare for our transition to current accounts. As current accounts will offer more options, we reorganised the app so features are grouped a little more logically (top up with card settings, sending money with your contacts), rather than overwhelming the home page with too many things.

column10: Can't recommend enough! Travelled to the USA for a week and used my Monzo card for most purchases and withdrawals and didn't have any issues, exchange rate is great based on MasterCard and no charges for purchases or withdrawals. Can also use the the UK if you have any money left over from a trip abroad.
Love it, but top up is buried.
Everything works excellently, customer service is excellent and app is excellent

After waiting for more than a week, I got this card. After seeing multiple negative reviews, I was little worried as I was planning to use this for my weekend trip to Norway. But it worked excellent and no issues anywhere.
The app is great shows spending very quickly. The big banks could learn something from this app
I love Monzo. Helps me budget and works amazing internationally. Super happy. Can't wait for the current accounts.
The future!
Amazing
Amazing app with very good client support but still needs some improvements

Got this for travelling- so easy to use and no fees! Ive been recommending it to all of my friends as a cheap and easy way to take travel cash. The Monzo team are fabulous, keeping us informed and not shying away from letting customers know if there's a problem and why. Can't wait for when the current accounts are available!
So easy to use and was informed on any potential problems if only all banks was like monzo. Recommend this card to all

Great MasterCard exchange rate. Just came back from holiday in Sicily and it never let me down. Top up on the go and balance available in seconds. App shows you the excact location where you spent the money and the type of business. Really top top app and 5 star service.
Brilliant customer service! The chat option is so useful~ I forgot my pin and they got back to me almost immediately and sorted it out for me. Would recommend!

Couldn't recommend Monzo Bank more. They are still a long way from their end goal, but the app is already packed with useful and innovative features and you can rest assured that this bank will get better with every passing day! Don't miss out.
Great app and card. Best card to take aboard. Gave me better exchange rate than the other cards.

Great modern future of banking. Gave me great rates abroad, better than the exchange rates I was getting at home. Back in the UK, amazing way to track your spending, still getting used to instant notifications, they're unbelievable.
Great card, great service, great app

Can't speak highly enough of this card, a must have for any overseas travel.  Essentially works as a debit card where you load money into it from your bank account.  Amazing for travel since it has no transaction fees, and gives you the MasterCard exchange rate, which is as good as you'll get.  App is very user friendly, loading the card with money is quick and you get instantaneous notification of any transactions.
Love the fact this is free of charges bravo I may do a YouTube video on this.
Banking done properly
Whats with the ios menu bar on android, could have done without that for some real features to close the gap between the two versions.
column15: Thanks for the feedback, John. We found that some key features were hard to find as they were hidden behind the drawer or FABs. As Google's design guidelines now include bottom navigation as an option, we gave it a go. So far it seems to be helping more people find things like peer-to-peer payments. Hope this helps explain!

column10: Good app for tracking your spend, was happy with it until 2 weeks back when they started sending notifications from TFL in the middle of the night UK time (2 am, 2:20 am, 2:40 am, 4 am) After communicating this to the Monzo team, the response was that they are not controlling the time that notifications are sent (whoever knows a little bit about this knows that it can be easily easily controlled in the thier backend) and that i should stop the notifications if it is bothering me. This is not a professional way to handle a customer! I have recommended this app multiple times, but my recommendations STOP here. Disappointing!
New update is great! Just needs spending limit options.
This is dope! Free onlinr non-uk purchases on AliExpress. Yeaaaa
Really convenient app and overall great experience!
No support for Russia
Really cool! Would be nice to have some security, like PIN or fingure print to open app

I signed up as I was about to embark on a month long trip and it got good reviews for a travel card. I ordered it on the Sunday and it arrived by the Tuesday. After travelling through five separate countries (five separate currencies) , I have had zero issues and now considering to use it as my daily account. I can't recommend this service enough. Keep up the hard work :)
Love the simple and intuitive design and service

Monzo work flawlessly! Customer service is always perfect and they reply extremely quickly to any query. The card itself works great in the UK & internationally and the app is ideal for tracking your spendings.
Best banking app out there
Good app to track your expenses live.
This card is the way it should be. I have used it in Holland and France and have not had a problem what so ever. I love my Monzo Card.

Monzo has incredible potential and once it launches a debit card for customers and sorts out some teething problems that come naturally with beta apps, I'll quickly make it my primary bank account. As a frequent traveller I make use of the card internationally, and it's so simple to track my spending on the move. The support team are also quick to respond - numerous times I've never had to wait more than fifteen minutes to hear back.

Why the need to have the back of a uk driving licence as well as the front. You have enough information with address, DOB and then you want photo ID, sounds like stealing people's ID for your own gains!!!💩💩💩💩💩💩💩💩💩💩💩💩💩💩💩
Excellent customer service, convenient to use and handled my card loss easily and professionally. Will definitely use again.
Super easy, aesthetically appealing way to manage money.
Love the card and the live updates/alerts. Would love to make my own categories for spending (like work etc)
Great mobile bank. Highly recommended

Really wish I could use Monzo as my default, and I totally would - were it not for their logistical issues / seriously incompetent support team. My card was sent to the wrong address 3 times in a row. Every time, I know it's about to happen & even warn them, but to no avail. Exciting start-up that has lots of growing up to do.
column15:
Sorry you've been having troubles getting set up, Nick. I just spoke to our Customer Operations team, and they're working hard to ensure your card gets to the correct address - signed, sealed, delivered 💌 

Hope you enjoy the app once you get rolling. Do let us know how you get on.

column10: Amazing app. Amazing service behind. Prompt customer service at any time of day / night / weekend / bank holidays. Recommend.
Using this for Interrailing and it's amazing. Company seems to be on the ball.
How banking should be done!
Cant see merchant expuse codes.

Great app for tracking your spending! You can top up the card easily on the app from a connected debit card. When you make a purchase you instantly get a notification and you can categories the purchase as well as writing little notes to remind you what the purchase was. Really great app!
Love it..
Easily the best debit card I've had used it all around south Korea recently, no problems. Can't wait for them to release bank accounts!
Very pleased with monzo

Initially I got the card for when travelling in Europe as it's far cheaper to use than my Bank card. Now I'm using it for almost all daily purchases. Rarely do I use my bank card anymore. I can track all spending, as soon as I make a transaction the app notifies. I wish they would hurry up and offer a full current account! Very impressed with what these guys are doing.
Beautiful app. What mobile banking should have been in the first place. Almost embarrassed to have such a lovely polished useful app next to the other fairly useless banking apps I have.
It would be nice to put our personal picture on the profile , it will be useful in other country's when they request ID prove
Opens quick and does what you want it to do. Really good.
Love the app! It would be nice if the iPhone features were brought over a bit faster though, it feels like we're months behind 😥.
Excellent, just come back from Florida and found it worked everywhere with no problems at all including the notifications apart from in First Class on the virgin 747-400 ....
Implement pin code or access code to access the application on mobile..just in case someone lost their phone ...MORE SECURE!!

Brilliant application. Let's you get ahold of your daily spending. No more opaque lines on a bank statement, and wondering where it all goes. Automatically categorises items, has views for spending per month, and lots of other goodies. And when spending money abroad you get the MasterCard rate (better than any bank!), with no additional fees. Brilliant!
Not one to write reviews but these guys deserve one. Customer service is the best ive had in london, app and service is simple and easy to use. Would recomend to everyone
Ive signed up numerous people but have only been bumped up once. Get me bumped up ASAP!
Brilliant app (when it works). They really need to get a grip with the intermittent problems that are plaguing card payments.
Can't use it unless you top up £100. Use the app Called "Loot". It's exactly the sane and you get your card without needed to deposit anything.
Really helpful app to check your payment and to control your finances.
Easy app to set up and works great with the bank card too
Perfect at keeping on top of your budget in real time!
So far so good. 5th star will be awarded once I use the card abroad and the app shows the details of those pay outs.
Very slick all the way through, from applying for the card, activating and using the app. Perfect!
Everything works flawlessly, no complaints!
I just love it! It simply changes your way of dealing with money and tracking your expenses. Simply perfect when traveling with a friend or when you're abroad.
Love using this. Only thing is I like using android pay so would be good to have that, but other than that a great app.

It's the best bank I've ever used!  They let me know immediately when my card declined with reason. Also, you can ask any questions by chatting with the staff 24/7 !!  And the way they categorise my spending is absolutely good not like Barclays or Lloyds or Tsb. It's an innovation.

Ditched my Caxton for this. Just used my monzo card for a month in USA and it worked 100% of the time even when swiping for fuel at petrol stations, love it! Love getting my transactions instantly as app notifications, makes it very easy to keep track of everything!
Good app, great idea, would be better if could change currency to the country you're visiting and balance is converted using current exchange rate to show how much you're using and have left
Entered security code to active account. When I press submit code nothing happens. It doesn't seem to send. Tried on 2 phones. No overlay on either fone customer service have no idea why......
It asks me for my passport details but I put them in and it doesn't accept them
Game changer, watch this space!

Amazing this is much better than any banking app. Notifications as soon as a payment has left contactless you get told straight away instead of having to wait up to 3 days for it to be taken out of your bank account. Perfect loving the app

It's great so far! It's contactless, top-ups are instant, transactions appear in real time, insights in your spendings. Conversion rates are incredible, no hidden fees. Looking forward to getting a bank account. I may ditch HSBC who can't keep up with the technology
I'm having trouble topping up, it keeps declining my bank eventhough I definitely have money on my debit card... Never had this problem! What the hell?!
A bank that cares about you. What else do you need from a bank?

Changed my phone, I can't login to my account the app says that they sent an magic email to myslef when I click on the link the app will pop up and showing me that I have 24700 people in front of me!!! I need to login not to create account
Useless app. So much hype but  no substance. Don't see the aim of this app. Good at nothing.
A Great Innovation. A must have App for all !

I don't really get the point of this app. It's like revolut but with half the features, and you can't use any of them while you wait in a queue of 30 thousand people to get a card printed. The app is also in beta, so it advises you to carry a spare card in case this one doesn't work?   No FSCS protection and no separate currency balances (both of which revolut already has).  Revolut also gives you your electronic card with card number instantly, so you can use it online while you wait for the physical card (which only took a couple weeks during the ultra high demand period, judging by the queue I'll be here at least a year before I can actually USE the monzo app or card). It's fully developed and stable. All payment notifications are instant.   Get revolut instead. It's the same but actually useful!  Monzo also requires you to send £100 to their non FSCS protected account before they'll print your "free" card. How about no?
App won't even let me verify. Customer service is useless and I want my £100 pounds back!! Don't download.
Fantastic app, never once crashed, instant transaction notifications.   If it becomes a fully fledged current account and fscs protection it would be perfect. Also password protection would be ideal.
I closed my and I went with Starling Bank who they offer current accounts
Best banking app on the market hands down! Thoroughly recommend it as it also helps to keep track of what you're spending :)
Absolutely amazing app keeps you on track and help at hand with customer service all ways at hand. Easy to use and much much more
Can't beat a clever/sarcastic customer service rep to motivate you into writing a negative review.

Can't use the app because my Gmail account is from Spain, I change it to UK ( because is where I actually live) but still saying in Spain you haven't launched the app. Any idea how to fix this and start using monzo?
Pure awesomeness. Highly recommended!
This Card is amazing and the conversion rate is fantastic. I will never ever go on holiday without it. Great Job Monzo
I just got monzo I'm really liking it I do payments I get a ping this will be good when I'm out drinking or even just shopping great job can't wait for current accounts c:

The app camera doesn't focus on documents so can't verify myself and have money in the account ! Emailed twice and told to take a photo of my documents.. Which like I said the app camera doesn't work well!

Would have been 5 stars this morning. Forced to update before using. I used the app yesterday and there was no warning of this. Forced to download over 3G while abroad, not cool. Very good otherwise though.
Great app and concept, simple and effective much better than my current bank. Can't wait for the current account to go live.
The complete solution to all your banking needs, particularly spending abroad.
Probably the best app I have.
Good in the USA also good in Spain.
Love it

I haven't used the iPhone app so I don't know what extra functionality it offers over the Android version. However, the android app seems rather basic and mainly serves as a record of your transactions. You can top up and send payments to other Monzo card holders but that seems about it. The app is simple to use and looks nice. I did have a problem with activating my card but the technical support was superb. Fast, friendly and they even updated the app to address the problem the very next day. The technical support was definitely 5 stars!
Great app

Elegant, flawless app (albeit less feature rich than the iPhone version). Excellent customer service. A virtually zero cost solution for travelling that helps you to keep track of your spending while giving you the peace of mind that you can withdraw cash if you need it. Can't wait for the full bank account.
Couldn't even get past ID recognition stage as app continually failed to recognise ID despite having appropriate permissions

What I would love to see is the same functionality that iOS users get whereby they can set spending limits (targets). Please don't forgot us Android users. Remember, there are more people using Android then iOS.
Love it
Its easy to use and really clean
Best banking app around.

Monzo is simply brilliant. The international conversation is the best you can get, and it immediately notifies you how much you spend in local and your currency. Its a great way to track your spending too, and topping up is easy.
Using the card overseas was smooth and easy and didn't incur any additional charges. Also their customer service is top notch!
Why does this app need camera and audio recording permission?

Great contactless card, nice and clean android app. Amazing how quickly you get notifications when you pay for stuff. Really easy to pay friends with also (I find it way quicker then paypal for instance). Really nice to use in place of an oyster card when i occasionally go to that Landaan.
I didn't even know what I was looking for until I found Monzo. Great for budgeting and tracking spending. Great when travelling abroad. Great at looking awesome and fluro orange.
Best bank... Can't wait for the current account
Great service and thanks for the continuous updates on Android.
Love it. Great way to track monthly spending
Really poor tacky "What's New" comments when this app stills remains feature lacking compared to iOS
Great app and bank. Instant view of payments, and helps track spending. Love it.

Installed this app on my Samsung S6 and I have tried to order a card but it won't allow me to submit the verification code. It literally does nothing when I type in the number and press submit. Contacted help and they told me to uninstall the app. This did nothing. Just contacted them again and they have given me the same advice. Hopefully it can be fixed.
Monzo is a fantastic banking service. If they maintain the current level of customer service while expanding it will be hard to beat.
Missing a yearly overview report
Awesome app! But could maybe add a export function?
Still no targets for android. Revolut card is wining the race and availability like Portugal.
This app and prepaid card is very useful and I made a mistake when transferring money over to my monzo account and this was fixed and explained to me within an hour. Amazing customer service.

Would be a 5* review if this app had the same features as the iOS version but for some reason Android loses out. No budgeting features, profile photos, spend graphs. It's a brilliant app still, but a shame to see android losing out to iOS on features.

Absolutely pointless. It's just another pre-payed "credit card" and not only that, you have to top it up with £100 before you can use it! I've heard so many stories about the software on Android being totally inferior to the iOS version rendering it virtually useless. Smells of a scam. Avoid!
Revolutionary! The categorisation of spend is a good send - such a simple, effective idea that's been implemented very well. Roll on the current accounts...
your chat forum is broken and I need to unlock my card. what am I meant to do?

My issue is with the development, or lack of, of the Android app. Supposedly iPhone is being developed first, and then ported to Android. That's fair enough, but I feel as though the Android app is being neglected while the iPhone app gets further ahead. 8 months later and I still have a very basic list of transactions with a predetermined list of categories. That's it.
Great app and great customer service. Managing spending made easy!

column15: We use camera and microphone for identity verification, and storage to save  the video/picture you take in this process. There should be a security process a code for you to use to get into just incase someone else goes into your phone and can easily access it without your permission... This is a major security risk although yes it's awesome to get access to but still not secure... I suggest adding a 4 or 5 digit code to access the app in order to make it secure which would also protect fraud issues...   Referred a few people still at the same number as I was... This wait better be worth it... But a suggestion for the developers instead of having to wait in a cue starting at the screen everyday release a preview of the app so people can see what monzo is like. Loved the app and the instant notifications so I knew how much I'd spent exactly in dollars and pounds on that transaction and it meant I could track my money. Usually when I travel with cash it seems to just go and I don't know exactly where it's gone but with this I could track every penny. Definitely want to carry on using it now I'm home just can't wait till they bring out their current account. Highly recommended!

Monzo is a really innovative banking company and their app is excellent in this respect. Their services are still in Beta and so of course there are restrictions regarding the pre-paid card, but it's clear for anyone considering the long-term impact, Monzo will really shake up the banking industry.  The current verson of the app allows you to manage your pre-paid card (used whilst the company awaits the removal of the restrictions on their banking license), view/categorise/annotate your transactions, get incredibly quick support (I've had responses in 5 minutes from employees), top-up and more. It can only improve from here, and so far the features such as the push notifications and intelligent purchase data retrieval (location of store, type of purchase etc) is really impressive and certainly not something I've seen with any other bank.  It would appear a lot of other reviewers don't understand Monzo particularly well, and that's fine - the bank isn't for everyone and is still in testing. I feel that the reviews section deserves unbiased opinions from those who value technical innovation though, and the above is just my two cents. I highly recommend Monzo.
